What is Variable?

Variable is the Name Of Memory Locations where we can Store our data.its values may be Numbers,Alphabets or 
Words the name of that memory location must be in characters or set of characters 
Once You store the value on that loaction then we cannot change it but it can be reused.

A variable can have alphabets, digits, and underscore.
A variable name can start with the alphabet, and underscore only. It can't start with a digit.
No whitespace is allowed within the variable name.
A variable name must not be any reserved word or keyword, e.g. int, float, etc.

for Example:- Num,input,St etc any alphabet or words can be a Varible 

Syntax:- Type Variable_list;

What is Data Type?

Data type tells that What type of data You stored in a Variable it may be integer,Float,or string etc 

Some Basic DataTypes:- Int, Char, String, Float, Long, double ,Array, Etc 

Synatax:- Type_Variable_Name 


examples:-   Int Number ;                     Here Int is a Integer data Type and Number is a Variable 
             Float Num                        Here Float is a data Type and Num is a Variable
             

             
